William Faulkner

Profession: Author and Nobel Laureate

Biography: He is known for his works such as "The Sound and the Fury," "A Fable" in 1954 and his last novel in 1962 "The Reivers", for which he won the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction.

Born: September 25, 1897

Birthplace: New Albany, Mississippi, USA

Generation: Lost Generation

Star Sign: Libra

Died: July 6, 1962 (aged 64)

Married Life

Author William Faulkner (31) weds Estelle Oldham at College Hill Presbyterian Church outside Oxford, Mississippi

Historical Events

William Faulkner completes his novel "Light in August"

William Faulkner's collections of short stories, "Go Down, Moses", is published

Nobel Prize for literature awarded to William Faulkner "for his powerful and artistically unique contribution to the modern American novel"

William Faulkner says US school degenerated to become babysitters
